This paper is about a machine learning technique for medical image segmentation, specifically MRI scans. The paper focuses on the development of a convolutional neural network that can perform segmentation without relying on modality labels. This work is highly relevant to the computer vision community (cs.CV) as it involves image analysis and segmentation. Additionally, the use of neural networks makes it likely that this paper could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on medical imaging and segmentation could also make it relevant to the neural engineering community (cs.NE). Finally, the use of multiple modalities in the segmentation process could make this paper relevant to the multimedia community (cs.MM).
